Well, mine shipped today, and all I can say is I just hope it lasts as long as my 2012 ultimate MBP that made it over 4 years strong. It's one of the only computers that made my life easier and relieved stress when we were on the road shooting for example, and until a month ago when the screen started tearing didn't have me feeling like I was falling behind. Edited 4k footage out of most of the cameras we'd be using on the road just fine (RED, FS7, C*00 etc). 

Maybe I am jaded, or maybe my experiences lately have lent me to be less reliant and obsessed with owning the technology but rather more stoked that the technology works for me and not the other way around, but this unboxing had me reflecting about when 'things' used to get me similarly ramped up. They don't anymore, pretty grateful for that. I am sincerely hoping for this young lady's best interest this is all marketing and her show for entertainment purposes. There's meaningful work to be done, there's a really sick world out there right now, and if digital media/social media professionals would put half this much enthusiasm into the efforts to make actual substantial change with these tools, we'd be in a much better place today.

Congrats on your new computer though, I didn't make it to the loud typing. Hopefully it's not as bad as all the commenters are saying. 

At the end of your unboxing, try to keep it in perspective- it still had the same OS as all of your other mac computers, and it will do the same job they do, albeit maybe more efficiently. If you catch yourself staring at it with an overwhelming unexplainable sense of joy, go outside, find some fresh air, meditate, drink a cold glass of water- do anything to get away from the illusion of material worth. It just doesn't matter- if I had half as many followers as you did, the things I could be doing for the Lakota at Standing Rock right now- such a powerful voice, being expelled and heard by half a million people, to validate a purchase you made online. 

We can do better.
